  fhir:differential [
     fhir:element ( [
       fhir:id [ fhir:v "DV_CODED_TEXT" ] ;
       fhir:path [ fhir:v "DV_CODED_TEXT" ] ;
       fhir:short [ fhir:v "A text item whose value must be the rubric from a controlled terminology, the key (i." ] ;
       fhir:definition [ fhir:v "A text item whose value must be the rubric from a controlled terminology, the key (i.e. the 'code') of which is the `_defining_code_` attribute. In other words: a `DV_CODED_TEXT` is a combination of a `CODE_PHRASE` (effectively a code) and the rubric of that term, from a terminology service, in the language in which the data were authored. \n\nSince `DV_CODED_TEXT` is a subtype of `DV_TEXT`, it can be used in place of it, effectively allowing the type `DV_TEXT` to mean  a text item, which may optionally be coded. \n\nMisuse: If the intention is to represent a term code attached in some way to a fragment of plain text, `DV_CODED_TEXT` should not be used; instead use a `DV_TEXT` and a `TERM_MAPPING` to a `CODE_PHRASE`. " ] ;
       fhir:min [ fhir:v "0"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger ] ;
       fhir:max [ fhir:v "*" ] ;
       fhir:isModifier [ fhir:v false ]
     ] [
       fhir:id [ fhir:v "DV_CODED_TEXT.defining-code" ] ;
       fhir:path [ fhir:v "DV_CODED_TEXT.defining_code" ] ;
       fhir:short [ fhir:v "The term of which the  `_value_` attribute is the textual rendition (i." ] ;
       fhir:definition [ fhir:v "The term of which the  `_value_` attribute is the textual rendition (i.e. rubric). \n" ] ;
       fhir:min [ fhir:v "1"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger ] ;
       fhir:max [ fhir:v "1" ] ;
       fhir:type ( [
         fhir:code [
           fhir:v "http://openehr.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/CODE-PHRASE"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           fhir:l <http://openehr.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/CODE-PHRASE>
         ]
       ] ) ;
       fhir:isModifier [ fhir:v false ]
     ] )
  ] . # 

